Cut the @onion{1} in half through the root and peel. Chop half the onion into 1cm pieces and the remaining half into ¼cm pieces. Remove the tops (tubey bits) of the @fennel{1} bulb and leave to the side for later. Cut the remaining fennel in half through the root, then remove the tough root. Cut each half in half again, then slice into 1cm wide slices. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}), finely chop the stalks of the @coriander{3}(chopped, stalks reserved) (leave the leaves for later).

Bring a #pot{} with @water{350%ml} to the boil with the @star anise{1} and @salt{pinch}. Once boiling, add the @basmati rice{1}, turn the heat down, put a #lid{} on for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and leave to rest for ~{10%minutes} with the lid on, or until the rest of the meal is ready.

> Tip: If the rice is ready before everything else, it doesn't matter, it will wait!

== Moqueca Sauce ==

Put your bigger pieces of onion in a #pan{} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and cook on medium heat for ~{5%minutes}, before adding your chopped fennel to the pan. Stir everything together and cook for another ~{7-10%minutes}. Season with a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{pinch}.

Once the 7-10 mins are up and your vegetables are soft, add the @tomato puree{2}, garlic, chopped coriander stalks and half the @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp} (use less if you don't like spice). Cook for another ~{1%minute} then add the @vegetable stock pot{1} and specified water to the pan. Bring to a gentle boil, stirring to dissolve the stock pot. Once simmering, turn the heat down slightly and simmer the mixture for ~moqueca sauce{10-15%minutes}.

== Paprika Cod ==

Mix the rest of the @smoked paprika{1/2%tsp} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #bowl{} then put the @cod fillets{2} in the bowl too. Season each fillet with a pinch of @salt{} and a grind of @black pepper{} and then mix until it's nicely coated in the paprika marinade.

== Salsa ==

Now it's time for your salsa! Put a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} in a bowl. Grate in the zest of the @lime{1} and squeeze in half the lime juice (use less lime if you're not a huge citrus fan!). Mix together with a #fork{}. Roughly chop the coriander leaves and chop the fennel tops (the ones put aside in step 1), as finely as you can. Put them both in the bowl with the lime dressing. Put your small pieces of onion in the bowl as well and then mix everything together.

== Cooking the Cod ==

Put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, place your cod in the frying pan skin-side down and cook for ~{3-4%minutes} before turning over and cooking for ~{3%minutes} on the other side (you don't need extra oil in the pan).

> Tip: To get crispy skin on the fish, don't move it around while it's cooking!

== Serving ==

Add your remaining lime juice to your moqueca sauce and stir together (use less lime if you're not a huge citrus fan!). Serve your rice in #bowls{} with your moqueca sauce. Place your cod on top and then spoon over a generous portion of salsa! Enjoy!